It wouldn't get you any more than a Standard Support Sona. It just comes down to how much of an impact you make. I know people who go Full AP Sona and justify it by saying her Utility and Heals scale with AP, but at the same time one way or another you can't afford to get Rabadon's over a Sightstone so you might as well do an AP-Utility build.

{{item:3009}} {{item:3050}} {{item:3222}} {{item:3504}} {{item:2301}} {{item:3116}} 

This has plenty of AP in it, 40% CDR (45% with the Mastery) and plenty of Utility without just getting Utility for the sake of Utility.
